Description.Text: Located in an imposing Edwardian building, this London hotel has been sensitively restored after a £15 million refurbishment programme to its original architectural style. Its 330 rooms feature modern, classic interiors and the latest technology, ideal for both the business and leisure traveller. The stylish Aston bar and restaurant takes its name from being the site of the inaugural meeting of the Aston Martin Club and is a popular venue in Fitzrovia. The Grafton offers the ideal location for those seeking the convenience of being in the centre of London near Euston Station, Oxford Street shopping, Theatreland, Regent's Park, Fitzrovia and Charlotte Street, Madame Tussauds and the Planetarium and Camden Town market and nightlife, Bloomsbury, Covent Garden and Soho's clubs, bars and restaurants.***The hotel is undergoing soft refurbishment from 01/08/11 till 14/11/11. The main bar lounge will be out of commission during this period. The restaurant area will remain unchanged. Access will be via the doors near the concierge desk in the lobby. After breakfast each morning, the restaurant will be transformed into a restaurant/bar area for our regular and in-house guests. As part of the refurbishment project, the main lobby staircase will be under refurbishment. There will be minimal noise disturbance during this period and no impact to the hotel�s accommodation rooms.***
